content.original: A thermobaric or Fuel Air Explosion (FAE) explosion occurs when fuel is aerosolized with a scattering charge and then detonated. The resulting explosion is significantly more energetic than a conventional high explosive of the same mass. While the name suggests an incendiary effect the fuel is detonated not burnt. The heat is immense but of very short duration; however flammable materials are likely to be ignited. Primary damage is caused by the massive blast followed by a near vacuum in the area, which quickly collapses. The shockwaves are devastating to structures and armored units. Exposed personal who are unlucky enough not to be vaporized by the blast often die slowly, lungs and eardrums ruptured by the catastrophic pressure differentials. Ammo Bins contain the rounds needed for projectile-based weaponry, with at least one bin required per weapon type. Upon receiving a Critical Hit, any remaining ammunition stored inside an Ammo Bin will explode dealing damage to the install location. Risk can be mitigated with the use of C.A.S.E.

content.content: 当燃料用散射装药雾化后引爆时,会发生温压或燃气爆炸(FAE).由此产生的爆炸比相同质量的常规高爆炸弹能量大得多.虽然其名称暗示了燃烧效应,但燃料被引爆而不是燃烧.在极短时间内放出大量热;并且,易燃材料可能被点燃.主要的破坏是由大规模爆炸造成的,随后该地区出现了会迅速崩溃的真.冲击波对建筑物和装甲单位造成破坏性伤害.非常不幸的没有被爆炸蒸发无防护人员通常会缓慢死亡,肺和耳膜因灾难性的压差而破裂.弹药舱包含射弹武器所需的弹药,每种武器类型至少需要一个弹舱.在受到严重损伤后,储存在弹舱中的任何剩余弹药将爆炸,对安装部位造成伤害.使用C.A.S.E.可以降低风险.
